 BUNNY</A> at: 8/28/02 11:26:37 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#aaaaaa><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/bpolykarbonbbs.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=synner>Synner</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/29/02 4:31:30 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4307.topic&index=5>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.boomspeed.com/synner/ryuavatar.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New drawing style</span><hr size=1> Well the only advice I can give, is find pics in the style u like, and draw from them. It is okay to do straight out copies for a while, because that is getting you used to the style, but try to add some more of yourself into each pic. I have no particular artists style that I follow, I used to draw spawn and youngblood ages ago, but I liked anime style, so I learned that (over a long period of time), now my pics are a convenient mix of both genres, and I like my stuff. Personalise your style, if you like pokemon style then draw that, and eventually modify it to your liking, it should come naturally with practice.<br>
<br>
I hope I helped, but I don't think I did. lol. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#CCCCCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub25.ezboard.com/upencilsoldier.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Pencil Soldier</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Karbonite</span><br> <font color=#336699>(8/30/02 1:54:26 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub25.ezboard.com/fpolykarbonbbsfrm2.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4307.topic&index=6>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.liquid2k.com/iambob/Shoroder.GIF height=100 width=130></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: New drawing style</span><hr size=1> dont copy peoples stuff!!how you suposed to get this style if you couple other people!?<br>
